<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="106" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,655,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,491,906,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[506,591,906,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–29" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1790,1814]" captionTargetBox="[164,1420,197,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-22@12.[151,1436,181,1766]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–29. Distribution of Punia species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413577/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Top End of the 
<collectingRegion box="[785,992,907,933]" country="Australia" name="Northern Territory" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Northern Territory</collectingRegion>
where it is known only from Katherine and the South Alligator River crossing north-west of Pine Creek township. The distribution given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moulds, M. S." box="[1270,1436,943,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" refId="ref14282" refString="Moulds, M. S. (1990) Australian cicadas. New South Wales University Press, Kensington. 217 pp., 24 pls." type="book" year="1990">Moulds (1990)</bibRefCitation>
includes other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moulds" authorityYear="2012" box="[319,386,979,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Punia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[319,386,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Punia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. Adults have been taken from late November to mid January, the only exception being one of the 
<typeStatus box="[314,362,1015,1041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">type</typeStatus>
series, which is labelled as having been taken on 12th July, a record that requires confirmation. Adults inhabit grass, tending brown rather than green.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,655,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
